			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Equipment suggestions please!<a name="73194"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 14 05 4:56 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>a huge part of learning to pull oow and GoD has to do with the worst pathing ever.
<br />

<br />
basically.. in the days of old... mobs had a set path they simply *had* to follow to get from one location to another.
<br />

<br />
players were &quot;exploiting&quot; this .. and it didn't seem very realistic either.
<br />

<br />
so.. since those days.. they've introduced dynamic pathing.  so mobs can follow you just about anywhere, by following the most direct route to you.
<br />

<br />
the problem is that it introduced insane insaine omfg insane warping.  i know you've seen it - esp in outdoor zones where there are hills, rocks, buildings, etc to get stuck on.  and in ldon... where there are doors to get stuck on.  the mobs will get stuck and warp to you.  sometimes they'll wait a moment, and sometimes they'll do it *immediately*.  this happens *very* often in riftseeker's sanctum and qvic.
<br />

<br />
at this point, you can do 1 of 2 things.  you can either die repeatedly and flame sony in /feedback and /bug... or you can realize they're not going to do a d*mn thing about collision (which by this point should be *very* apparent) and learn to work with it.
<br />

<br />
we're bards.. which makes us extremely versatile in our playstyles.
<br />

<br />
one of the cooler things about us is that we run really.. really fast.  this isn't just a perk.. it's a pulling tool.
<br />

<br />
now... what i'm about to tell you has been considered by some whiners as &quot;exploiting&quot;... but it's really learning to work with the way sony has made the game.. and refuses to do otherwise =)
<br />

<br />
alright say you're in qvic.. and you're trying to pull dvoin m'sha, without first clearing the rest of his house.
<br />

<br />
what do you do?  you move everyone to the little tower over near zoo and tell them to hang tight.
<br />

<br />
you then selos up... head toward dvoin's house... and DA song right when you get to the ramp.  run up and sit next to her to expidite agro.
<br />

<br />
run out of the house asap and back toward the madrona zone in area... before DA vanishes.  eventually she'll warp (she gets stuck on her doorway)... but you'll also have a lot of much faster running mobs after you.
<br />

<br />
the cool thing is that she warps to about the pit area.  this is when you fade.  it's really tough to tell when she does this.. so you gotta be on the ball... but if you have SoE or DMF... and selos going... you'll basically outrun all the other mobs.. she'll be a good distance behind them.
<br />

<br />
at this point you circle around the pit (asap before things start pathing)... and use the hos - bellow - fade trick and grab her, leading her back to the tower.
<br />

<br />
takes all of about 30 seconds.
<br />

<br />
my point being...
<br />

<br />
if you try clearing the rest of the house to get to her and expect things to come willingly and nonwarpingly (new word!) you're going to die every time as you wait for just *one* mob to come.. because they're going to warp.. and they're going to warp into friends more often than not.
<br />

<br />
best thing for you to do is learn *how* and *where* and *when* they warp... and turn that to your advantage.
<br />

<br />
hope this helps at all =\
<br />

<br />
gear is a factor.. but not as great of one you might think.  it's mainly paying attention, crowd control, and nimble fingers =p
<br />

<br />
good luck hehe
<br />

<br />
ferr</span></td>
