				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Equipment suggestions please!<a name="73216"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 14 05 1:58 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Actually, warping in GoD and OoW is almost exclusively the fault of the Z-Axis.  You can warp a mob halfway across the zone by standing on the zone wall or even a large hill/rock.
<br />

<br />
Most important thing?  Stay out of Wall of Slaughter.  This place is horrid exp, stupid trains, and draws far more people than the zone can support.
<br />

<br />
As far as why you're dying?  Probably because you're getting hit<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  With 3800 base hiptoints, even fully buffed, mobs in MPG will 1 round you.  But you probably already know this since you're asking for advice.
<br />

<br />
For Alternate Abilities I would make sure you have Fading Memories, Natural Durability, and Physical Enhancement.  Next I would train Run Speed to the max.  Max Combat Agility, Lightning Reflexes, and Reflexive Mastery.  The mitigation (combat stability --&gt; innate defense) AA rely quite a bit on your Armor Class, so as your AC goes up train these.  Regeneration is another important series of AA to get.  With 45 worn regen and alot of aa regen I can regenerate most damage back while pulling, believe me...it helps tremendously.
<br />

<br />
It's tough to not train the &quot;fun&quot; stuff.  Ie.. crits, nuke crits, etc..  But really you need to live to dps.  With low FT you won't have the mana regen to fade off ramp every time.  So you are going to have to absorb ramp damage from nocs etc..  Stay away from the light for now! (&quot;fun&quot; aa!)
<br />

<br />
If you have a steady exp group, you might consider moving them to Ruined City of Dranik.  You can hit the zone itself or either of the instanced zones off of RcoD.  Pickup some random drops, named drops, and quest items on top of good, fast exp.  You're going to take less abuse here than you will in MPG.
<br />

<br />
You're elemental flagged, why don't you have any elemental armor?  This is going to be your best outlet to get quick and easy gear.  Soak it all up, don't wait for any particular piece.  If you're KT flagged I would hit up the ikkinz 1 group trials for new haste (get rid of that belt!), a new ring, and a new ranged item and if you're lucky some hp and/or shielding augments.
<br />

<br />
Once you have 6-6.5k unbuffed hp you can start to pull in mass exp and loot in MPG, Riftseekers, and MPG Trials.  Until you have the hp/ac you are just going to be brutalized in these zones.
<br />

<br />
Some examples of quest items in RCoD:
<br />
[url=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=31972]Dragorn Crest Amulet[/url]
<br />

<br />
[url=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=31602]Muramite Officer's Ring[/url]
<br />

<br />
For crying out in the dark why can't there be some sort of standard on message boards for url linking.  Fug it, here are the urls:
<br />

<br />
